caption: Had the Philly cheese steak sandwich, best I can remember..

I was disappointed that it said they were open only to walk 2 miles to a closed stall. Was really looking forward to the epic looking menu. Maybe try to keep that updated...so hungry gluten free folks aren’t caught unawares
Always a FIVE! Love, Love Love!!!
Longer wait. Not the best Muffalettas.
Great food and sweet people! 💚

Really good sandwiches and salads! I was a little hesitant to order food from a stall in the French Market that mostly caters to tourists, but the quality and portions were very good. And the prices are fair.
Ladies and Gentlemen, the best tuna sandwich in the world! =)
Very delicious vegetarian options.
The most divine gluten free muffaletas ever! This is always my first stop when I get to New Orleans. My husband orders their regular muffaletas, they are delicious too!
My sandwich was sooo delicious and the woman working the counter was very sweet. I will come back to try more of the menu!
My favorite place for delicious mediterranean food. The staff was very helpful and observant. It has a nice atmosphere.
Good food
Muffuletta was great! I'm usually not a fan of olives but they were perfect.

Rude lady and I'm praying I don't get sick. Took forever to get 2 sandwiches and some pita bread. She wanted to debate every cheese choice we tried to make for the 3 cheese plate. We finally just said forget after telling her we know the flavors we wanted and she still pushed other cheeses we didn't want.

The woman at the register was very kind and was really the one who made me consider eating here. I got a egg sandwich—cheddar, spinach, and 2 eggs on a croissant. Soooooo good! Highly recommend for breakfast. Best part is, she walked this meal over to where I was sitting across from the restaurant. Very sweet.
An excellent muffuletta!! Highly recommend stopping in here for a muffuletta and then strolling around the French Market. The olive salad is perfection!
So glad they are open again. Always a great muffuletta. Thank you.
Hands down the best muffulettas in New Orleans. I will make the drive from Houston just to taste the olive spread and cheese goodness. Try it. TRY IT.

We were ready to try our first Muffuletta when we noticed they can make any sandwich Gluten Free.  They won our vote. 2 people split a 1/2 and it was plenty. The olive salad was perfect. And the staff was fantastic and engaging.
A little pricey ($5 beer) but the muffaletta ($9 for half) was excellent! Very limited seating as in open French Market area. Thanks.

This place is yummy! When I didn't want to use a plastic cup for my champagne the Chef insisted on proper glasses, so sweet of him!  The food and service were equally outstanding.  I can't wait to return!
Great selection and good stop for a drink.
The vegetarian muffuletta is easily one of the best sandwiches I’ve ever had in my life.
Great gluten free options and the Muffuletta is a must.

So so so good!!!   Need a break from deep fried everything, crawfish, gumbo, and general tourist trap food?  Definitely eat here then, this place made us feel healthy and normal again.  Thank you for saving us!!!!  We had the goat cheese salad with apples and pistachios, as well as the vegan muffuletta.  Highly recommend!
Friends recommended this place. And it did not disappoint.  Muffuletta was delicious.  Prices are very reasonable.
Love it

Best Muffaletta sandwich I’ve ever had! They can make it gluten free, vegetarian, and even vegan! The vegan sandwich comes with hummus and avocado instead of meat and cheese. They made the hummus to order and it was so flavorful. I can’t even imagine how great this melty local specialty would be with the salami and provolone!
Had a great sandwich.  Manchego and serrano ham. Gluten free as well. Wine good. Roast beef sandwich was good according to wife. Will go back. Its south of the market in the food strip.
Delicious sandwiches!!

Me and a friend were shopping on a budget, looked into this place and got a $5.44 Muffaletta and a $5.25 grilled cheese. Both were incredibly good. One of the best sandwiches I've ever had was that Muffaletta. If you are anywhere near, come check it out.

One of the best meals I had in NOLA. I got the muffaletta, my mom got a 2 cheese grilled cheese with gouda and mozzarella on multi-grain. Both were hand-delivered to us at the little table we snagged right next to the counter. The muffaletta was epic. I would go back there for another one in a heartbeat. It was so juicy and flavorful. If I hadn't gone to Cafe Amélie for dinner it would have been my best meal in NOLA, but you can't really compare a sandwich for lunch with an epic dinner, just saying. Still if I find myself in NOLA again I would definitely hit this place up again for lunch or even an early dinner, yes, yes, and more yes.
It was packed but the food was great!
Really good muffaletta
Gluten-free muffuletta is amazing!
Excellent muffuletta!

I'm actually writing a review while waiting for my food. I'm a Nola resident and love my city. I'd be the first to admit that the customer service here is sorely lacking but people are known for their friendly, welcoming demeanor - always open for a kind gesture or chit-chat. This place is neither welcoming nor friendly, even to those who live here. Hope the $11gluten-free smoked salmon sandwich is worth the unfriendly attitude.
Great sandwiches Salmon sandwich was really good

Omg sandwiches here especially the Mochago and Seranno ham sandwich (prosciutto sharp spice cheese olive oil mixture in a baguette) is just to die for. Fresh ingredients decent prices everything top notch. After trying not so good sandwiches and food in the area this was definitely a breathe of fresh air and a total head turner
amazing sandwiches and very reasonably priced - a must visit!

Best muffulettas in French Quarter, hand made by Italians daily. Ice cold beer, wine, breakfast available in the French Market.lots of sandwiches to choose from, wash it down with a mimosa or sangria.

A guy at one of the tourist centers recommend this place for the muffulettas. He was not wrong. I have tried a few muffulettas, but Alberto's is truly the best one I have ever had. We also tried a couple if salads, which were also excellent. All of their food is very fresh and perfectly seasoned.  We continue to come here and recommend it to anyone else of our friends that go to NOLA.
One of my favourites in New Orleans and definitely the best place in French Market. Highly recommended
Tasted muffaletta there. Strong flavor of garlic, fresh olive in olive oil. Unlike central grocery, they serve it warm, which I think intensifies the flavor.
Wonderful breakfast sandwiches.  Great quality,  just like home !
Our food tour guide took us here for the muffaletta and we're so happy she did. The sandwich was out of this world and it was nice to do something not on Bourbon Street.
VERY BEST MUFFALETTA, the only one I ever want to eat!  You must give it a try!
The best Muffuletta in town!! INCREDIBLE!
I go here every time in New Orleans. Everything is good but the mufaletta is the best.
Excellent breakfast. I had the mushroom, brie and ham omelet. My wife had a spinach, Swiss and bacon. Price less than 10$.

I went to Alberto's to try the muffaletta and it was definitely worth it. Alberto's serves it as a warm sandwich (some places serve it cold or warm).  It was delicious, and big - the half size is all you need. We also had a bit of banter with the lovely lady working there; teasing us that we would not be able to finish a half each. We did! IG: @easty_eats

This is one of the places that was recommended.  We got the muffuletta with ham instead of salami for $6. It was good but compared with other food around here, we thought it was average.  It was hard to get a table but we like the atmosphere here.

I had there Muffuletta sandwich and it was great.  My might had the veggie Muffuletta and she really enjoyed it.  My wife had the chorizo sandwich.  All of the food was really good quality. I would definitely go back there if I'm in New Orleans again.
Best muffuletta ever! As a local, I promise this.
Fabulous muffaletta! Get you one!
Always fresh made to order. Tasty.
Incredibly delicious muffaletta!!! The sangria is also delightful. Would definitely recommend you stop here!!!

The quality of the food was average and the cooking not impressive considering the many fabulous options available in New Orleans.  After waiting in line for a long time, the lady at the counter was rude, while taking my order she stopped several times to talk to other people who had been standing in line behind me and my family.  Then she asked me to sit at a nearby table so that she could deliver our food but then when the food was ready about 30 minutes later, she had us pick it up ourselves.  I had already paid and tipped the restaurant 20%.  My family and I will never visit Alberto's again and will definitely not recommend it to our friends.
We had 1/4 Muffuletta and 1/2 Tuna. Both were excellent. Highly recommend the Muffuletta even if you don't like olives! 1/2 can be shared by 2 people.
Friendly service and the best muffuletta!!!! The 1/4 serving is perfect as a meal. Olive spread is amazing.

I absolutely adore this bistro in the French Market. The best muffuletta I've had in New Orleans. So many things I look forward to trying in the future too, but I'm not a local. Alberta and Juan have been there every time I've visited. Check this place out and get a New Orleans classic...just look at the picture of it!
We ordered the muffaletta, 1/2 an order was the perfect bite to share with my husband.
Muffuletta was one of the best. Add on the Mimosa, and you have a piece of happiness. 6$ drink 5.99 for quarter of a sandwich.
One of my favorite lunch time places...  Best pick is the Manchego or the Smoked Salmon sandwich good price great service
Servers are fast!!
Overcharged for products that we did not even ask for. Strongly avoid this place at all.
Good food and small price.

So delicious! I split the Manchego and Serrano Ham sandwich with a friend. It was so simple, with toasted bread and some olive oil, but amazing. It's in the French Market and is easy to miss if you're not looking at the signs.
Both the muffalta and the service were top quality. Served in a warm bun, as expected!
The best!!
Nice staff, very helpful.
This was a winner!  I want to hear back in the afternoon for a cheese tray and a bottle of wine.
Loved that I was able to get a muffuletta on gluten free bread, it was delicious!
(Translated by Google) Excellent food and first class service  (Original) La comida Excelente y el servicio de primera
Good sandwiches and drinks.
An unexpected cheese board delight in the middle of the market place.
The best muffaleta in new orleans with a mediterranean touch. You must taste it!!!
